Both files emitted. Key finding: the cohort contains a tightly-defined responder subgroup of ~1,790 patients (3.6%) with response rate **78.6% vs 16.5%** outside it (Fisher OR=18.55).

**Subgroup definition:** `feature_001 = 1 AND feature_014 = 1 AND feature_021 = 1 AND feature_026 = 0 AND feature_009 = 0`

The three positives form a symmetric three-way synergy (any one of them can be treated as the "treatment", with the other two as predictive biomarkers — the heterogeneity is identical). Two binary suppressors (feature_026, feature_009) each individually nullify the responder effect when positive. Within the subgroup, lower `feature_004` and lower `feature_020` further intensify response. The transcript walks through 25 iterations of hypothesis-test-refine cycles validated by split-sample reproducibility.
